// symlink-agents configuration.
//
// Roles -- reason from these keys, not from the default paths (every path here
// is configurable):
//   - symlinkToDirectory / symlinkToFile: the real, committed source of truth.
//     Defaults: .agents/ and AGENTS.md.
//   - symlinkFromDirectories / symlinkFromFiles: where generated symlinks are
//     created, each pointing back at the source so a tool finds files where it
//     expects them. Defaults: .claude/ and CLAUDE.md.
// A link lives at a "from" path and points at the matching "to" path (ln -s
// semantics): "to" is always real, "from" is always generated. Nothing forces
// .agents/AGENTS.md to be the source -- you could instead make .claude/CLAUDE.md
// canonical and generate the rest, just by swapping which paths go in to/from.
//
// include / exclude decide which paths inside a "from" target are shared
// (replaced with a symlink into the source) versus left real and tool-owned.
// Patterns are gitignore-style globs; the most specific match wins; on a tie
// exclude wins; an unmatched path falls back to "default". A pattern matches by
// subpath: a bare name like "skills" applies to every target, while prefixing it
// (".claude/skills") scopes it to one. "default" sets the polarity: "exclude"
// shares only what include lists; "include" shares everything except what
// exclude lists.
//
// How to extend this safely:
//
// Sharing a path only makes sense if its contents are PORTABLE -- the same file
// must stay valid when another tool reads it through the symlink. Never assume;
// read the target tool's own up-to-date docs and check two things:
//   - Format: an open, cross-tool standard every tool parses the same way, or a
//     tool-specific schema/frontmatter another tool would misread? Share only
//     standards.
//   - Ownership: authored, committed, shareable content -- or runtime config,
//     generated state, mutable memory, or local/private data? Keep the latter
//     real.
//
// To add a tool: put its directory in symlinkFromDirectories, apply both checks
// to each surface, include what carries over, exclude the rest. When unsure,
// leave it excluded; real is the safe, reversible default.
{
	"symlinkToDirectory": ".agents",
	"symlinkToFile": "AGENTS.md",
	"symlinkFromDirectories": [".claude"],
	"symlinkFromFiles": ["CLAUDE.md"],
	"default": "exclude",
	"include": ["skills", "agents", "commands"],
	"exclude": [
		".claude/CLAUDE.md",
		".claude/settings.json",
		".claude/rules",
		".claude/output-styles",
		".claude/workflows",
		".claude/agent-memory",
		".claude/agent-memory-local",
		"**/*.local.*",
		"**/settings.local.json"
	],
	"gitignore": true,
	"vscode": true,
	"zed": true,
	"noteDefaultIncludeDrift": true
}
